Dear friends,

(=C7=E1=CA=D1=CC=E3=C9 =C7=E1=DA=D1=C8=ED=C9 =C3=CF=E4=C7=E5)

Greetings from Stockholm! I hope this finds you all well and safe. The worl=
d continues to see many challenges, and the last weeks have been particular=
ly difficult in many different places, including some were you all live. Ho=
pe everyone is managing ok, and that you find strength and support from fam=
ily, friends, and colleagues.

Thanks to all of you who participated in the series of network meetings tha=
t we held a few weeks back! It was lovely to see you all and to hear how ev=
eryone was doing. Also great to get everyone=92s thoughts and ideas about h=
ow you want to use our network structure this coming year.

I am writing today with three key updates about the year. You will get info=
rmation about our digital meetings, our in-person meeting, and about our sp=
ecific activities. There is quite a lot of information in this e-mail and I=
 kindly ask you to read through it all, as there are also some questions th=
roughout the e-mail that I would appreciate your answers to.

Before getting into those things though, I am also happy to share an encour=
aging update. As you know, we have been spending a lot of time in the begin=
ning of this year trying to secure additional funds for our work. This morn=
ing, we received a letter saying that one of our funding applications have =
been approved! This was the funding we had applied for to do a fourth cohor=
t of the learning and exchange program. So in the coming months, we will be=
gin recruitment for the next group. If you already have people in mind that=
 you think would be good participants, please let me know!

Digital meetings

Based on your feedback in the last network meeting, we will arrange a digit=
al meeting every other month. This means that this year, we will have one m=
eeting in June, one in August, one in October and one in December.

For each occasion, we will suggest two time slots and you show up to the sl=
ot that works best for you. One of the members of the facilitation team, Na=
bil, we contact you shortly to arrange the dates for the first meeting.

We will use the meetings to share updates, learn about what is going on in =
our different contexts, and provide some training opportunities on specific=
 topics.

In addition to the regular meetings, some of you expressed an interest to m=
eet digitally in smaller, possibly country specific groups. For those of yo=
u who are interested in this, could you please reply to this e-mail and let=
 me know if you would also be willing to coordinate and host these meetings=
?

In-person meeting

We will host our in-person meeting this year in September or October. This =
will be our one in-person gathering for this year. Some of you expressed a =
desire to meet in-person more often. Unfortunately this is not possible due=
 to the funding constraints that we are facing this year, but we will work =
to make it possible in the future.

For the in-person meeting, I would like to start checking your availability=
. Please write back to me and let me know which of the following dates woul=
d work for you:

September 12-15

September 19-22

September 26-29

October 3-6

October 10-13

Our group is quite large now and I am sending you multiple suggestions for =
dates with hope that we can find one option that work for as many people as=
 possible. Please let me know all the dates that you are available, and try=
 to be as flexible as possible.

Specific activities

As you know and as was mentioned during our last meeting, we are also plann=
ing to run some specific activities in the different countries this year. T=
here are different timelines to these and different ways of being involved.=
 Some of you already have been in meetings about these activities and some =
of you are still waiting to hear how you can be involved. Given that these =
activities are country specific, the easiest thing to do if you are interes=
t in knowing more is to contact me directly and I can give you the informat=
ion about the activities in your country. As the year continues, I will als=
o continue to be in touch about these things but if you want to know more a=
lready now, please don=92t hesitate to contact me. There are also people in=
 our network who are taking specific responsibility for these activities, a=
nd I can point you to them as well for more information.

Lastly, if you have additional ideas (meaning ideas other than those that w=
ere discussed at our network meeting in Hammamet last year) for specific ac=
tivities that you would like to implement this year, please let me know. As=
 a reminder, below is a short text with the explanation of what these activ=
ities are for:

=93In addition to running a capacity-building program (component 1) and mai=
ntaining a network comprised of those who completed this program (component=
 2), SweFOR=92s work in the Maghreb region also includes providing support =
to strategic interventions that seek to influence specific key driving fact=
ors of conflict (component 3).

The strategic interventions are undertaken together with partners in the di=
fferent contexts and can involve both offering targeted support to some of =
their ongoing interventions as well as designing and implementing new initi=
atives. These interventions can be led by the partners themselves, by SweFO=
R, or jointly=94.

So if you have ideas in line with the criteria above that you and/or your a=
ssociation wants to implement, do let me know! The approach to change in ou=
r project is based on coming together for learning, exchange and networking=
, and then on all of you taking that learning and network back to the work =
that you are doing in order to make that stronger. From SweFOR=92s side, we=
 can provide more targeted support to activities that you suggest if there =
is an added value to such support.

Thank you for reading through all of this and looking forward to hearing fr=
om you all.

My very best,
Erik




